{
  "text": "The combined application of SKA-31 and ACh induced additive effects evident at lower but not at higher concentrations at which a solid hyperpolarization to near the K + equilibrium limits the dilator response. Despite the effects being mainly additive, SKA-31 may still restore endothelial function in situations of impaired ACh-dilation [CITATION_1] or in case of an upregulated K Ca 3.1-mediated pathway [CITATION_2] because SKA-31 potentiated ACh-induced dilations also in other species or vascular beds without 2012-BJP-1040-RP.R2",
